name: New infrared view of the Horsehead Nebula — Hubble’s 23rd anniversary image
description:
This new Hubble image, captured and released to celebrate the telescope’s 23rd year in orbit, shows part of the sky in the constellation of Orion (The Hunter).

Name:	Barnard 33, Horsehead Nebula
Type:	Milky Way : Nebula : Appearance : Dark
Distance:	1300 light years
Constellation:	Orion
Category:	Anniversary Nebulae

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.

Credit: ESA/Hubble/NASA
